 Myocardial ischemia is a common cause of death in North America and proper
 monitoring of the patients is important.
 The most common monitoring technique involve ECGs and a simple average
 over a small section of the heartbeat.
 We were the first to propose wavelets as a tool to measure ischemia.
 Having several perpendicular measures of the same physiological phenomenon
 typically allows one to improve accuracy.
